sentences: Philip Catherine (born 27 October 1942) is a Belgian jazz guitarist.
Philip Catherine was born in London, England, to an English mother and Belgian father, and was raised in Brussels, Belgium.
He released his debut album, Stream, in 1972.
During the next few years, he studied at Berklee College of Music in Boston and with Mick Goodrick and George Russell.
In 1976, he and guitarist Larry Coryell recorded and toured as an acoustic duo.
The same year, when Jan Akkerman abruptly left Focus, Catherine replaced him in the band.
The following year, he recorded with Charles Mingus, who dubbed him "Young Django".
In the early 1980s, he toured briefly with Benny Goodman.
During the 1990s, he recorded three albums with trumpeter Tom Harrell.
